HEADWORD: Sessile-eyed
<hw>Ses"sile-eyed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having eyes which are not elevated on a stalk; -- opposed to
<contr>stalk-eyed</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sessile-eyed Crustacea</b></col>, <cd>the
